    "answer_id" : 68976118,
    "question_id" : 46091927,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This code worked for me. all date are in <code>LocalDate</code> formate.</p>\n<pre><code>JPAQueryFactory jpaQueryFactory = new JPAQueryFactory(entityManager);\nreturn jpaQueryFactory\n                .from(qAccVoucherMaster)\n                .leftJoin(qAccVoucherMaster.accFinancialYear, qAccFinancialYear).fetchJoin()\n                .where(qAccVoucherMaster.voucherDate.between(fromDate, toDate))\n                .fetch();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2533010,
      "reputation" : 791,
      "user_id" : 2200883,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 76,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/kS2MA.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Mohammad Hammadi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2200883/mohammad-hammadi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1719498869,
    "creation_date" : 1719498869,
    "answer_id" : 78678304,
    "question_id" : 46091927,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You have to use Expressions.asDate as follow:</p>\n<pre><code>return queryFactory.from(timeSheet)\n        .where(Expressions.asDate(timeSheet.date).between(fromDate,toDate))\n        .fetch();\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
